text: Physical Education Building/La Crosse State Normal School was the original physical education building at the La Crosse Normal School, now the University of Wisconsin–La Crosse, in La Crosse, Wisconsin. The building was constructed in 1916 and was named Wittich Hall after one of the school's physical education professors, Walter J. Wittich.UW–La Crosse Wittich Hall It was designed by architects Parkinson & Dockendorff. ==References== Category:University and college buildings on the National Register of Historic Places in Wisconsin Category:Buildings and structures in La Crosse, Wisconsin Category:University of Wisconsin–La Crosse Category:School buildings completed in 1916 Category:Gyms in the United States Category:National Register of Historic Places in La Crosse County, Wisconsin Category:1916 establishments in Wisconsin
